-- Abraaj’s Arif Naqvi Appointed to UN Advisory Body Global Compact
-- B y   A r i f   S h a r i f
-- 2012-05-01T09:49:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-01/abraaj-s-arif-naqvi-appointed-to-un-advisory-body-global-compact.html
Arif Naqvi, founder and group chief
executive officer of private equity company Abraaj Capital that
manages more than $6 billion, has been appointed to the board of
Global Compact, an advisory body of the  United Nations .  Naqvi will join 13 business leaders from different regions
and industries on the body involving business, civil society,
labor and employers’ organizations, Dubai-based Abraaj said in
an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Arif Sharif in Dubai at 
 asharif2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  